import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import { Absolute, Box } from '../../lib'

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"absolute"}}>{`Absolute`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Hello, I'm a mdx file!`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={0} __codesandbox={`undefined`} __code={`<Absolute top={0} right={0}>
  <Box background="#CCC" height="100px" width="100px" />
</Absolute>
<Absolute top={0} left={0}>
  <Box background="#CCC" height="100px" width="100px" />
</Absolute>`} __scope={{props,Absolute,Box}} style={{height: '100px'}}>
  <Absolute top={0} right={0}>
    <Box background="#CCC" height="100px" width="100px" />
  </Absolute>
  <Absolute top={0} left={0}>
    <Box background="#CCC" height="100px" width="100px" />
  </Absolute>
</Playground>
<PropsTable of={Absolute} /></MDXTag>
